Ejercicio 1¶

El dataset de consumo_plantas.csv contienen datos que corresponden a 17 plantas electricas y el consumo de agua en galones que estas generan mensualmente.

  • Y: Consumo de agua en galones.
  • X1: Temperatura media mensual en grados Fahrenheit.
  • X2: Produccin mensual en libras.
  • X3: Nmero de das de operacin mensual.
  • X4: Nmero de empleados.
  • X5: No especificada.

Se pretende explicar el consumo de agua (Y) en funcin de las demas variables.

a) Use el paquete statsmodels.api y ajuste un modelo de regresin lineal usando mnimos cuadrados (OLS) y muestre la tabla con el resumen del ajuste. Qu observa en dicho ajuste?

e) Investigue y argumente como es que las componentes principales ayudan a mitigar el problema de la multicolinealidad severa.

Al realizar este proceso se ayuda a reducir el problema de multicolinealidad, ya que estos modelos tienen como objetivo encontrar unas nuevas variables regresoras que, en este caso, son las componentes principales, estas se obtienen a partir de la matriz de observaciones donde los datos iniciales se transforman en otras variables independientes de tal forma que no esten correlacionadas, y con estas se ajusta la ecuacin de regresin.

El argumento es el siguiente:

Partimos de la matriz de datos estandarizados $X^*$, se estima la matriz de correlacin $R$, que corresponde a la matriz de correlacin de los datos originales. $R$ se descompone $R = (L^*)^t \Lambda^* L^*$, sean $\lambda_1^*$, $\lambda_2^*$, ..., $\lambda_p^*$ los valores propios asociados a la matriz de correlacin y $\Lambda^*$ la matriz diagonal de valores propios y $L^*$ la matriz ortogonal de vectores propios.

Posteriormente, se genera la matriz $Z_{n \times p}^* = X^*L^*$ que contiene las componentes principales y cada una de las columnas de $Z^*$ define el nuevo conjunto de variables predictoras ortogonales, donde $(Z^*)^t Z^* = (L^*)^t (X^*)^t X ^* L^* = I$

def scatterPlot(plt,datasetPD,col_1,col_2,colorDots='darkblue',label=None,shift=0.05,**kwargs):
    dataPD = datasetPD[[col_1,col_2]]
    plt.scatter(dataPD[col_1],dataPD[col_2],color=colorDots)
    if(label!=None):
        points = datasetPD[[col_1,col_2,label]].values
        for point in points:
            plt.text(point[0]+shift,point[1]+shift,str(point[2]))
    plt.axvline(**kwargs)
    plt.axhline(**kwargs)

from matplotlib.patches import Ellipse
from scipy.stats import chi2

#Definimos algunas funciones necesarias
def computeMaximumLikelihoodEstimators(datasetPD,columns):
    mu =  list(datasetPD[columns].mean())
    sigma = np.matrix(datasetPD[columns].cov())
    return mu, sigma

def diagonalize(sigma):
    eigenValues, eigenVectors = np.linalg.eigh(sigma)
    idx = eigenValues.argsort()[::-1]   
    eigenValues = eigenValues[idx]
    eigenVectors = eigenVectors[:,idx]
    return eigenValues, eigenVectors

def plotConfidenceEllipse(plt,mu,eigenValues,eigenVectors,chiSquaredCriticalVale,ax=None,**kwargs):
    if ax is None:
        ax = plt.gca()
    theta = np.degrees(np.arctan2(*eigenVectors[:,0][::-1]))
    width,height = chiSquaredCriticalVale*np.sqrt(eigenValues)
    confidenceEllipse = Ellipse(xy=mu,width=width,height=height,angle=theta,**kwargs)
    ax.add_artist(confidenceEllipse)
    return confidenceEllipse

def getProbabilityDensityContour(plt,datasetPD,columns,alpha,freedomDegrees,color,name='DataSet'):
    mu, sigma = computeMaximumLikelihoodEstimators(datasetPD,columns)
    eigenValues, eigenVectors = diagonalize(sigma)
    chiSquaredCriticalVale = chi2.ppf(q=(1-alpha),df=freedomDegrees)
    plotConfidenceEllipse(plt,mu,eigenValues,eigenVectors,chiSquaredCriticalVale,color=color,alpha=0.25)
    sumaryTable=[]
    sumaryTable.append(['Mean',mu])
    sumaryTable.append(['Covariance matrix',sigma])
    sumaryTable.append(['EigenValues',eigenValues])
    sumaryTable.append(['EigenVectors',eigenVectors])
    sumaryTable.append(['Confidence',1-alpha])
    sumaryTable.append(['Chi-squared critical value',chiSquaredCriticalVale])
    sumaryTableDF = pd.DataFrame(sumaryTable,columns=['Summary',name])
    return sumaryTableDF

Ahora, para encontrar la ecuacin de la recta de separacin ($\textit{frontera de decisin}$), recordemos que para dos variables, se tiene que:

$$ ln\left(\frac{p(\mathbf{x})}{1-p(\mathbf{x})}\right) = \beta_0+\beta_1 x_1 +\beta_2 x_2 \quad \quad donde:$$
Parmetro Valor
$p(x)$ 0.2307
$\beta_0$ 36.9477
$\beta_1$ 0.6680
$\beta_2$ -0.6258
$$\Rightarrow \frac{ln\left(\frac{p(\mathbf{x})}{1-p(\mathbf{x})}\right) -\beta_0-\beta_1 x_1}{\beta_2}=x_2$$$$\Rightarrow x_2=\frac{ln\left(\frac{0.23}{1-0.23}\right) -36.94-0.668 x_1}{-0.625}=\frac{ln\left(\frac{0.23}{1-0.23}\right)\:-36.94}{-0.625}+\frac{0.668}{0.625}x_1$$$$\therefore x_2=61.037+1.06x_1$$

Ahora vamos a calcular los parmetros restantes

  • F-score con $\beta$=1
$$F_{c}(\beta) = (1+\beta^2) \frac{TNR_c TPR_c}{(1+\beta^2)TNR_c+TPR_c}=\left(1+1^2\right)\frac{\left(0.9\right)\left(0.75\right)}{\left(1+1^2\right)\left(0.9\right)+\left(0.75\right)}=0.52941$$
  • Odds Ratio
$$DOR_c = \frac{TPR_c TNR_c }{ FPR_c FNR_c}=\frac{\left(0.75\right)\left(0.9\right)}{\left(0.07692\right)\left(0.25\right)}=35.10140$$

Fall out:
$$FPR_c = \frac{FP_c}{FP_C+TN_c}=\frac{1}{1+12}=\frac{1}{13}=0.07692$$ Miss Rate: $$FNR_c = \frac{FN_c}{FN_c+TP}=\frac{3}{3+9}=\frac{1}{4}=0.25$$

%matplotlib inline

def compute_frequencies(dataset_df,col,index=None):
    if index is None:
        index = 'index'
    columns=[col,'freqs_'+col,'relative_freqs_'+col]
    freqs_df = dataset_df.reset_index()\
                .groupby(col)\
                .count()\
                .reset_index()[[index,col]]\
                .rename(columns={index:'freqs_'+col})
    
    freqs_df['relative_freqs_'+col] = freqs_df['freqs_'+col]/len(df)
    freqs_df= freqs_df[columns].sort_values(col)
    missings_counts = df[col].isna().sum()
    missings_df = pd.DataFrame([['Missings',missings_counts,missings_counts/len(df)]],columns=columns)
    freqs_df = pd.concat([freqs_df, missings_df])
    return freqs_df

new_train_tpr = [0,0,0,0,0] 
new_train_fpr = [0,0,0,0,0]
new_test_tpr = [0,0,0,0,0]
new_test_fpr = [0,0,0,0,0]

for i in range(0,len(train_tpr)):
    new_train_tpr[i]=(train_tpr[i]-train_fpr[i])*(1/pow(2,1/2))
    new_train_fpr[i]=(train_tpr[i]+train_fpr[i])*(1/pow(2,1/2))
    new_test_tpr[i]=(test_tpr[i]-test_fpr[i])*(1/pow(2,1/2))
    new_test_fpr[i]=(test_tpr[i]+test_fpr[i])*(1/pow(2,1/2))

%matplotlib inline

def compute_frequencies(dataset_df,col,index=None):
    if index is None:
        index = 'index'
    columns=[col,'freqs_'+col,'relative_freqs_'+col]
    freqs_df = dataset_df.reset_index()\
                .groupby(col)\
                .count()\
                .reset_index()[[index,col]]\
                .rename(columns={index:'freqs_'+col})
    
    freqs_df['relative_freqs_'+col] = freqs_df['freqs_'+col]/len(loans_raw_df)
    freqs_df= freqs_df[columns].sort_values(col)
    missings_counts = loans_raw_df[col].isna().sum()
    missings_df = pd.DataFrame([['Missings',missings_counts,missings_counts/len(loans_raw_df)]],columns=columns)
    freqs_df = pd.concat([freqs_df, missings_df])
    return freqs_df

from sklearn.metrics import  confusion_matrix, precision_score, recall_score, f1_score, accuracy_score

imputed_test_df.sort_values('score',ascending=True,inplace=True)
imputed_test_df['profit'] = np.where(imputed_test_df['target']==0,imputed_test_df['Principal'],-imputed_test_df['Principal'])
imputed_test_df['cumulated_profit'] = imputed_test_df['profit'].cumsum()
threshold_row = imputed_test_df[imputed_test_df['cumulated_profit'] ==imputed_test_df['cumulated_profit'].max()]
threshold_cutoff = threshold_row['score'].values[0]
imputed_test_df['target_est'] = np.where(imputed_test_df['score']>=threshold_cutoff,1,0)

precision = precision_score(imputed_test_df['target'],imputed_test_df['target_est'])
recall = recall_score(imputed_test_df['target'],imputed_test_df['target_est'])
f1 = f1_score(imputed_test_df['target'],imputed_test_df['target_est'])
accuracy = accuracy_score(imputed_test_df['target'],imputed_test_df['target_est'])

print('HEAD:')
display(imputed_test_df.head(5))
print('TAIL:')
display(imputed_test_df.tail(5))
print('OPTIMAL THRESHOLD CUTOFF SCORE VALUE:')
display(threshold_row)

plt.figure(figsize=(10,10))

plt.plot([1,0],[1,0], linestyle='-', color='Gray', label='Base Line')

plt.xlabel('Score')
plt.ylabel('Cumulated profit')
plt.legend()
plt.show()

print('PRECISION:',precision)

print('F-SCORE:',f1)

print('DENIED OPERATIONS:',len(imputed_test_df[imputed_test_df['score']>=threshold_cutoff]))
print('DENIED PERCENTAGE:',len(imputed_test_df[imputed_test_df['score']>=threshold_cutoff])/len(imputed_test_df))
print('ADMISSIONS OPERATIONS:',len(imputed_test_df[imputed_test_df['score']<=threshold_cutoff]))
